    "custom_liquid_WgJTim": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "name": "Custom Liquid",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": true,
        "remove_vertical_spacing": true,
        "remove_horizontal_spacing": true,
        "liquid": "<style>\n  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800;900&display=swap');\n\n  .cn-faq {\n    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;\n    padding: 48px 20px;\n    max-width: 720px;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n    background: #f7f8fa;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__title {\n    font-size: 20px;\n    font-weight: 900;\n    color: #0d1f3c;\n    text-align: center;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.04em;\n    margin-bottom: 28px;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__list {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 10px;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__item {\n    background: #fff;\n    border-radius: 14px;\n    border: 1.5px solid #e8e8e8;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    transition: border-color 0.2s;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__item.open {\n    border-color: #1a5cff;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__trigger {\n    width: 100%;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 12px;\n    padding: 16px 18px;\n    background: none;\n    border: none;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    text-align: left;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__trigger svg.cn-faq__icon {\n    width: 20px;\n    height: 20px;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    stroke: #1a5cff;\n    fill: none;\n    stroke-width: 1.8;\n    stroke-linecap: round;\n    stroke-linejoin: round;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__question {\n    flex: 1;\n    font-size: 14px;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: #0d1f3c;\n    line-height: 1.4;\n    letter-spacing: -0.01em;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__chev {\n    width: 18px;\n    height: 18px;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    stroke: #aaa;\n    fill: none;\n    stroke-width: 2.5;\n    stroke-linecap: round;\n    stroke-linejoin: round;\n    transition: transform 0.3s, stroke 0.2s;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__item.open .cn-faq__chev {\n    transform: rotate(180deg);\n    stroke: #1a5cff;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__answer {\n    display: none;\n    padding: 0 18px 18px 50px;\n    font-size: 13.5px;\n    color: #444;\n    line-height: 1.7;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__item.open .cn-faq__answer {\n    display: block;\n  }\n\n  .cn-faq__answer strong {\n    color: #0d1f3c;\n    font-weight: 700;\n  }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"cn-faq\">\n  <h2 class=\"cn-faq__title\">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n\n  <div class=\"cn-faq__list\">\n\n    <!-- Q1 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">How does the ChillNest work without water, gel, or electricity?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        The ChillNest uses <strong>self-cooling fiber technology</strong> — a triple-layer fabric that absorbs heat directly from your dog's body and disperses it into the air. The moment he lays down, the surface starts pulling heat away through conduction. No freezing, no filling, no plugging in. It resets on its own once he gets up.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q2 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">Is there any gel inside? What if my dog chews on it?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        <strong>Zero gel. Nothing to leak, nothing to chew open.</strong> This is one of the biggest reasons owners choose ChillNest over other mats. The cooling comes entirely from the fabric layers — no liquid fill, no chemical pouch inside. If your dog chews the outer fabric, there's nothing harmful underneath. You can also leave him unsupervised without worry.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q3 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">My dog keeps going to the bathroom floor or kitchen tiles. Will he actually use this?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        That bathroom floor behavior is exactly what the ChillNest is designed to replace. <strong>Dogs seek cold surfaces by instinct</strong> — they press their belly and paws against anything cool they can find. The ChillNest gives them that same sensation but in their actual spot. Most dogs find it within minutes. Put it where he already tends to go and he'll choose it over the tile.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q4 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">How long does the cooling last? Does it need to recharge?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        The mat stays cool for <strong>as long as your dog is lying on it</strong> — continuously dispersing heat throughout the day. When he gets up, the mat resets on its own within minutes. No putting it back in the freezer, no waiting period. It's ready again automatically.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q5 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">What size should I get for my dog?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        <strong>Size S</strong> — up to 20 lbs (Chihuahuas, Yorkies, small breeds)<br><br>\n        <strong>Size M</strong> — 20–50 lbs (French Bulldogs, Beagles, Corgis)<br><br>\n        <strong>Size L</strong> — 50–80 lbs (Goldens, Labs, Huskies, Collies)<br><br>\n        <strong>Size XL</strong> — 80+ lbs (German Shepherds, Great Danes, Mastiffs)<br><br>\n        If your dog is between sizes, <strong>always size up</strong>. Dogs tend to stretch out fully when they're hot — more coverage means more relief.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q6 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">My dog has a really thick coat. Does this actually help heavy-coated breeds?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        Yes — this is actually one of the most common use cases. <strong>Heavy-coated breeds like Huskies, German Shepherds, Golden Retrievers, and Mastiffs</strong> struggle most in summer because their fur traps body heat. The ChillNest works through conduction — pulling heat from the body through the belly and paws, which is exactly how dogs naturally try to cool themselves. Thick coat or not, it reaches them.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q7 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">I have no AC. Will this actually make a difference in a hot apartment?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        Yes — and it's especially useful without AC. <strong>The mat cools through direct contact</strong>, not by cooling the air around it. Even in a room that's 85–90°F, the surface stays noticeably cooler than the floor. It won't replace an AC unit, but it gives your dog a consistently cool spot to return to throughout the day — which makes a real difference in how well they cope with the heat.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q8 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">He pants all night and keeps me awake. Will this actually help him sleep?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        That's one of the most common things we hear from owners — and one of the most noticeable improvements. <strong>Panting at night is a direct sign your dog's body temperature is too high to settle.</strong> When his sleeping surface is actively drawing heat away, his body temperature drops, panting slows, and he can finally rest. Most owners report a calmer first night within the first use.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q9 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">Is it machine washable?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        Yes. <strong>Machine wash on cold, gentle cycle. Air dry recommended.</strong> The cooling properties are built into the fabric structure — not a coating or chemical treatment — so they stay fully intact after washing. No special care required.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q10 -->\n    <div class=\"cn-faq__item\" data-faq>\n      <button class=\"cn-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\">\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n          <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"/>\n          <path d=\"M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3\"/>\n          <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/>\n        </svg>\n        <span class=\"cn-faq__question\">What's your return policy?</span>\n        <svg class=\"cn-faq__chev\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"/></svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"cn-faq__answer\">\n        <strong>30-day money-back guarantee.</strong> If your dog doesn't take to it or you're not satisfied for any reason, contact us within 30 days of delivery and we'll make it right. No hassle, no complicated process.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n(function() {\n  var items = document.querySelectorAll('[data-faq]');\n  items.forEach(function(item) {\n    var btn = item.querySelector('.cn-faq__trigger');\n    btn.addEventListener('click', function() {\n      var isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');\n      items.forEach(function(i) { i.classList.remove('open'); });\n      if (!isOpen) item.classList.add('open');\n    });\n  });\n})();\n</script>",
